sql:
SELECT SUM(cost) AS total_servicing_cost
FROM vehicle_servicing
WHERE vehicle_id = 1;

SELECT servicing_id, servicing_date, servicing_type, cost
FROM vehicle_servicing
WHERE vehicle_id = 1;

SELECT v.name, v.vehicle_id
FROM vehicles v
JOIN vehicle_theft vt ON v.vehicle_id = vt.vehicle_id
WHERE vt.theft_date = (
  SELECT MAX(theft_date) FROM vehicle_theft
);

SELECT category_name, description
FROM vehicle_categories
WHERE parent_category_id IS NULL;

external_knowledge:
- 'Sold' listings indicate that the vehicle has been successfully sold;
- Servicing, accidents, and theft records provide insights into the vehicle's maintenance and history;
- Category information helps in understanding the type of vehicle.

- 'Top 5 sellers' refers to the sellers with the highest number of vehicles sold;
- 'Listing information' includes the listing price, date, status, views, and favorites;
- 'Sales information' includes the sale date, price, status, payment method, and payment date.

sql:
SELECT AVG(selling_price) AS average_selling_price
FROM vehicles
WHERE year > 2015;

SELECT v.name
FROM vehicles v
JOIN vehicle_theft vt ON v.vehicle_id = vt.vehicle_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Reported' accidents are those that have been officially reported to the relevant authorities;
- 'Active' insurance policies are those that are currently valid and in force;
- The year of manufacture being after 2015 refers to vehicles that are relatively newer models.

sql:
SELECT vehicle_id, listing_id, price, views, favorites, listing_date
FROM vehicle_listings
WHERE views > 50;

external_knowledge:
- 'Whisked away by the shadows of theft' refers to vehicles that have been reported stolen;
- 'Protective shields' refer to insurance policies;
- 'Current state' refers to the policy status.

- "individually owned" refers to vehicles sold by individuals;
- "manufactured between 2015 and 2020" refers to the year of manufacture;
- "average insurance premium" is the mean value of insurance premiums for a vehicle;
- "more than 3000 to be considered insurance-worthy" is a threshold for the average insurance premium.

- 'Completed' refers to services that have been fully performed and are not pending or in progress;
- 'Cost greater than 500' means the servicing expenses exceeded 500 units of currency;
- 'Most recent' refers to the latest dates in the servicing history.

- Seller types can be Individual or Dealer;
- The condition of the vehicle can be New, Used, or Refurbished;
- The category of the vehicle can include Sedan, SUV, Coupe, etc.
